ht_to_well-being_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1696945025 320w" width="1095" height="730" alt="World Mental Health Day 2023 A universal right to well-being - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="World Mental Health Day 2023 A universal right to well-being - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-1884_"/></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-6300" data-category="Generic Content" data-name="Matcha" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-hAcGzb jHOovW pf-1885_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-eGPXGI cIlovf"><div class="sc-iCfMLu eehqFj pf-1886_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px;--s-sm:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-XxNYO eWQzGj pf-1887_"><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-1888_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-1890_">Every year on October 10th, the global community comes together to shine a light on a topic often shrouded in silence: mental health. World Mental Health Day 2023 isn’t just a day of reflection; it’s a call to action. This year's theme is clear: 'Mental health is a universal human right'.</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-1891_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-1893_">The universality of mental health</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/The_university_of_mental_health_-_World_Mental_Health_Day_2023_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1696945134" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/The_university_of_mental_health_-_World_Mental_Health_Day_2023_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1696945134 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/The_university_of_mental_health_-_World_Mental_Health_Day_2023_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1696945134 320w" width="1949" height="1300" alt="The university of mental health - World Mental Health Day 2023 - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="The university of mental health - World Mental Health Day 2023 - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-1894_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-1895_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-1897_">You, me, our neighbours, the barista who serves us coffee every morning, the bus driver, the CEO, the intern; we all have one thing in common: mental health. It’s as much a part of us as our physical health. Yet, even in the modern age, the subject is met with whispers, if at all.<br><br>Today, we loudly and proudly declare: “It’s okay to talk about mental health and even more okay to seek help.” The Mental Health Foundation is leading the charge. Addressing inequalities in mental health services ensures that good mental health is not a privilege but a right for everyone.</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-1898_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-1900_">Tea, Talk and Transform</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Tea_Talk_and_Transform_-_Mental_health_is_human_rights_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1696945277" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Tea_Talk_and_Transform_-_Mental_health_is_human_rights_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1696945277 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Tea_Talk_and_Transform_-_Mental_health_is_human_rights_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1696945277 320w" width="1383" height="922" alt="Tea, Talk and Transform - Mental health is human rights - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Tea, Talk and Transform - Mental health is human rights - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-1901_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-1902_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-1904_">Imagine 260,000 people across the UK sitting down, sipping their tea, and breaking the barrier around mental health conversations. That’s exactly what’s happening through the 'Tea &amp; Talk' initiative.<br><br>Over 7,000 events have sprouted nationwide, turning ordinary tea sessions into extraordinary platforms for change. Each chat, each sip, is a step towards a society where everyone’s mental well-being is acknowledged and nurtured.</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-1905_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-1907_">Why the urgency?</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Why_the_urgency_-_Mental_health_awareness_-_World_Mental_Health_2023_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1696945483" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Why_the_urgency_-_Mental_health_awareness_-_World_Mental_Health_2023_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1696945483 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Why_the_urgency_-_Mental_health_awareness_-_World_Mental_Health_2023_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1696945483 320w" width="1643" height="1088" alt="Why the urgency - Mental health awareness - World Mental Health 2023 - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Why the urgency - Mental health awareness - World Mental Health 2023 - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-1908_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-1909_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-1911_">One may ask, “Why is this so important?”. Here's the stark reality:</span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-jHkVzv gbyaRg pf-1912_"><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-1913_">Children and adults in the lowest income brackets are 2-3 times more likely to develop <a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/collections/mental-health-courses-training-online-mental-health-courses/products/mental-health-awareness-online-package-cpduk-certified?variant=39536565157957" target="_blank"><i><span style="color: rgb(74, 144, 226);">mental health</span></i></a> issues than the highest.</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-1915_">38% of people with severe mental health symptoms also juggle long-term physical conditions.</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-1917_">Asylum seekers are 5 times more likely to have mental health needs than the general populace.</li></ul><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-1919_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-1921_">These aren't just numbers; they represent lives, hopes, and dreams. The glaring inequalities necessitate urgent action. Mental health disparities cannot and should not be the norm.</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-1922_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-1924_">A ripple effect of change</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/A_ripple_effect_of_change_-_Advocating_for_mental_health_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1696945579" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/A_ripple_effect_of_change_-_Advocating_for_mental_health_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1696945579 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/A_ripple_effect_of_change_-_Advocating_for_mental_health_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1696945579 320w" width="2000" height="1110" alt="A ripple effect of change - Advocating for mental health - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="A ripple effect of change - Advocating for mental health - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-1925_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-1926_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-1928_">Beyond Tea &amp; Talk, a movement occurs online and offline. Whether proudly wearing a green ribbon, engaging in robust social media conversations, or directly supporting affected individuals, every action creates ripples.<br><br>Sharing a story or even a simple photo, like on the @mentalhealthfoundation Instagram page, can be the lifeline someone needs. It's a gesture that says, “You’re not alone. We’re in this together.”</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-1929_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-1931_">Speaking up and reaching out</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Speaking_up_and_reaching_out_-_You_are_not_alone_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1696945655" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Speaking_up_and_reaching_out_-_You_are_not_alone_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1696945655 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Speaking_up_and_reaching_out_-_You_are_not_alone_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1696945655 320w" width="1600" height="900" alt="Speaking up and reaching out - You are not alone - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Speaking up and reaching out - You are not alone - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-1932_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-1933_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-1935_">Starting a conversation about mental health, whether your own or inquiring about someone else's, can be daunting. But remember, talking is therapeutic. Here's a brief guide:</span></p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cZMNgc bNHzPH pf-1936_">If you’re opening up:</h3><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-jHkVzv gbyaRg pf-1938_"><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-1939_">Choose a confidante, be it a loved one or even a helpline.</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-1941_">Find a comfortable place to converse. Sometimes, even a walk can be therapeutic.</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-1943_">Be prepared for varied reactions, and arm yourself with patience and information.</li></ul><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cZMNgc bNHzPH pf-1945_">If you’re reaching out:</h3><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-jHkVzv gbyaRg pf-1947_"><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-1948_">Ensure a distraction-free space for the conversation.</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-1950_">Listen more than you speak. Sometimes, all one needs is a patient ear.</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bQtKYq wvgEH pf-1952_">Offer help, but let them guide the process. Their journey, their pace.</li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-1954_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-1956_">The next steps</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/The_next_steps_-_Mental_health_awareness_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1696945923" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/The_next_steps_-_Mental_health_awareness_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1696945923 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/The_next_steps_-_Mental_health_awareness_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1696945923 320w" width="1880" height="1250" alt="The next steps - Mental health awareness - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="The next steps - Mental health awareness - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-1957_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-1958_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-1960_">Awareness is the starting point; action must follow. For anyone struggling, remember, you’re not alone. From GPs to helplines and community groups, avenues are waiting to assist. Embrace them.<br><br>For those fortunate to enjoy good mental health, take a moment to educate, support, and engage. Every gesture, however small, contributes to a world where mental health is not a privilege for a few but a universal right for all.<br><br>In the spirit of World Mental Health Day 2023, let’s stand united in ensuring everyone has access to the care, understanding, and support they deserve because mental health is a universal human right.</span></p><h2 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu NrNIR pf-1961_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyElHZ fxaypC pf-1963_">Conclusion: Uniting for a brighter tomorrow</span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Conclusion_Uniting_for_a_brighter_tomorrow_-_World_Mental_Health_Day_2023_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1696946334" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Conclusion_Uniting_for_a_brighter_tomorrow_-_World_Mental_Health_Day_2023_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1696946334 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Conclusion_Uniting_for_a_brighter_tomorrow_-_World_Mental_Health_Day_2023_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1696946334 320w" width="2000" height="1334" alt="Conclusion: Uniting for a brighter tomorrow - World Mental Health Day 2023 - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Conclusion: Uniting for a brighter tomorrow - World Mental Health Day 2023 - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-bXTejn eKvewz pf-1964_"/><p class="sc-FNXRL jGHEAN pf-1965_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gyE